<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Geographic distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Palaearctic region. The 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. nigricollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="nigricollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">E. nigricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
geographic range is in the northern part of Eurasia with the Yenisei River as the eastern border. In the tundra zone of Russia, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Lukin, EI" editor="Bykhovsky, B" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="195 - 467" refId="B24" refString="Lukin, EI, 1976. Leeches of fresh and saline waters (Fauna of the USSR. Leeches). In: Bykhovsky, B, Ed., Fauna USSR. Nauka, Leningrad: 195 - 467" title="Leeches of fresh and saline waters (Fauna of the USSR. Leeches)." volumeTitle="Fauna USSR." year="1976">Lukin (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, this leech is most widespread and numerous in water bodies of the Komi region and the eastern part of Arkhangelsk Region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="location">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Location.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">There is no specimen in our collection from the Kharbey area.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Nesemann, H" journalOrPublisher="Spectrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" refId="B29" refString="Nesemann, H, Neubert, E, 1999. Clitellata, Branchiobdellida, Acanthobdellida, Hirudinea. In: Schwoebeland J, Zwig P (Eds) Suesswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa. Spectrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" title="Clitellata, Branchiobdellida, Acanthobdellida, Hirudinea. In: Schwoebeland J, Zwig P (Eds) Suesswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa." year="1999">Nesemann and Neubert (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. nigricollis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="nigricollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">E. nigricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the potamal fauna and prefers large rivers; in contrast, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lukin, EI" editor="Bykhovsky, B" journalOrPublisher="Nauka, Leningrad" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="195 - 467" refId="B24" refString="Lukin, EI, 1976. Leeches of fresh and saline waters (Fauna of the USSR. Leeches). In: Bykhovsky, B, Ed., Fauna USSR. Nauka, Leningrad: 195 - 467" title="Leeches of fresh and saline waters (Fauna of the USSR. Leeches)." volumeTitle="Fauna USSR." year="1976">Lukin (1976)</bibRefCitation>
asserts that this leech is typical for small lakes and natural stagnant water bodies located in the floodplain of rivers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
